{
  "texts": [
    "The exponents α s, α d, and γ introduce non-linear scalings, such as crowding effects for the number of visits, where higher densities lead to sublinear (α < 1) or superlinear (α > 1) increase in flow.Figure 3b shows the values of the exponents obtained by fitting Eq.",
    "( 1) to the empirical flows F ij at different resolution levels N g (see Methods).",
    "We find a remarkable stability across grid sizes, with α s = 0.74 ± 0.15, α d = 1.04 ± 0.18, and γ = 1.12 ± 0.16 close to 1.",
    "We also note a trend where γ decreases with increasing resolution, though within error bars.",
    "This effect suggests a lower cost of distance for local jumps, creating a \"flatter\" distance distribution when considering a higher resolution."
  ]
}